body:
In the `else` branch of the `parse_type` dispatch in `nonreducer_axis`, `RUNTIME_ERR` sets a `RuntimeError` but does not return. Execution continues to `PyArray_Check(a_obj)` where `a_obj` is still NULL (its initial value) — dereference of NULL `ob_type`.

Currently unreachable (only 3 valid enum values exist), but a code change adding a new parse type without updating this function would trigger the crash.

**File(s):** `nonreduce_axis_template.c:640-642`

**Suggested fix:**

```c
// Before:
} else {
    RUNTIME_ERR("Unknown parse type; please report error.");
}

// After:
} else {
    RUNTIME_ERR("Unknown parse type; please report error.");
    return NULL;
}
```

See #518 for the complete report.

Found using [cext-review-toolkit](https://github.com/devdanzin/cext-review-toolkit).
